ReadMe

Script: notOnOpen()

Overview

This Google Apps Script scans the “Stocks & Flows” sheet in a Google Sheet, searches column G for the first TRUE value, and automatically scrolls the active view to that cell, ensuring it appears near the top of the screen.

Maintenance

To customize this script for your sheet, update the following values in the code:
	1.	Sheet Name
Replace "Stocks & Flows" with the name of your sheet:

var sheet = spreadsheet.getSheetByName("Your Sheet Name");


	2.	Target Column
Modify the column to search by changing the column index (7 for column G):

var columnG = sheet.getRange(1, 7, lastRow).getValues(); // 7 = Column G


	3.	Offset Rows
Adjust the +23 offset to set how far down the matched row appears:

var targetRow = Math.min(lastRow, i + 23);

How to Use
	1.	Run the notOnOpen() function from the script editor.
	2.	The script will:
	•	Locate the first TRUE in the specified column.
	•	Scroll the sheet so the matching row is visible near the top of the screen.
	•	Stop searching after the first match.

Troubleshooting
	•	Sheet Not Found: Verify the sheet name matches the one specified in the script.
	•	No Effect: Ensure the specified column contains TRUE values.
	•	Error: Double-check the column index and data range.